SIMPLE: connascency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Connascency
<hw>Con*nas"cen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>con-</ets> +
<ets>nascentia</ets> birth, fr. <ets>nascens</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>nasci</ets> to be born.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The common birth of
two or more at the same tome; production of two or more together.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is born or produced with
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of growing together.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Connascent</ent>⟦br⟧
